            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The lower section is blasted rock of fairly poor quality, though the upper half, which is natural rock, offers surprisingly good climbing. The biggest advantage is probably how quick it is to get there after work in the evening.\n\nA sketch can be found on Plonk (http://www.plonk.se/oldsite/munchen2.html)\n\nThe six or seven routes whose hangers/anchors were stolen in 2007 have now been restored to their former glory and are climbable again. Read more on Utsidan (http://www.utsidan.se/forum/showthread.php?t=43532)\n\nThe Bolt Committee replaced the hangers on Meja Madeleine's anchor on 12/7 08.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:munchenbryggeriet"
            ]
          }
        },
